<article class="page-container mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-12 py-10 text-base-content/80 lg:py-14">
  <header class="space-y-3">
    <p class="text-sm font-medium text-primary">About this theme</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-base-content">API Docs</h1>
    <p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
      A one-page theme for OpenAPI docs. The home page shows your API reference with Stoplight Elements.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="space-y-4 border-t border-base-300 pt-10">
    <h2 class="text-3xl leading-6 font-semibold text-base-content">1. What it is</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
      <li><span class="font-medium text-base-content">Template:</span> Api Docs (<span class="font-mono text-sm">index</span>)</li>
      <li><span class="font-medium text-base-content">Use case:</span> publish REST API reference from an OpenAPI JSON or YAML file</li>
      <li><span class="font-medium text-base-content">Layout:</span> fixed header + full-width API viewer</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4 border-t border-base-300 pt-10">
    <h2 class="text-3xl leading-6 font-semibold text-base-content">2. Add your API document</h2>
    <p>New sites start with a sample spec. To use your own:</p>
    <ol class="list-decimal space-y-3 pl-5 marker:font-medium marker:text-primary">
      <li>In Desk, open <span class="font-medium text-base-content">Pages</span> → <span class="font-medium text-base-content">Home</span> → <span class="font-medium text-base-content">Interface</span>.</li>
      <li>Copy your external OpenAPI <span class="font-mono text-sm">.json</span> or <span class="font-mono text-sm">.yaml</span> file.</li>
      <li>Paste it into <span class="font-medium text-base-content">OpenAPI document (JSON/YAML)</span> and save.</li>
      <li>Publish and view the home page.</li>
    </ol>

    <figure class="overflow-hidden rounded-box border border-base-300 bg-base-200/30">
      <img
        src="{{ 'images/theme/settings.png' | asset_url }}"
        alt="OpenAPI document field in the home page interface editor"
        class="w-full"
        width="1600"
        height="900"
        loading="lazy"
      />
      <figcaption class="border-t border-base-300 px-4 py-3 text-sm text-base-content/60">
        Paste your API JSON into the field above.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <p class="text-sm text-base-content/60">
      Tip: you can also set <span class="font-medium text-base-content">OpenAPI document URL</span> to load a remote spec instead.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4 border-t border-base-300 pt-10">
    <h2 class="text-3xl leading-6 font-semibold text-base-content">3. Preview</h2>
    <div class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-1">
      <figure class="overflow-hidden rounded-box border border-base-300 bg-base-200/30">
        <img
          src="{{ 'images/theme/index.png' | asset_url }}"
          alt="API docs home page"
          class="w-full"
          width="1200"
          height="900"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <figcaption class="border-t border-base-300 px-4 py-2 text-sm text-base-content/60">Home page</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="border-t border-base-300 pt-8 text-sm text-base-content/60">
    <a href="{{ site.pages['/'].path }}" class="link link-primary">Back to API docs</a>
  </footer>
</article>
